What you need to know:

Mori, an 83-year-old former prime minister known for public gaffes, told the Mainichi Shimbun he was sorry for his "thoughtless" remarks, which prompted calls for him to step downMori is reported to have said Wednesday that "board of directors meetings with many women take a lot of time", according to the Asahi Shimbun dailyTokyo 2020 has not responded to a request for comment on Mori's remarks, but has called a press conference for later Thursday that is expected to address the row